# No Push or Deploy Without Permission

Do not push to GitHub or deploy anywhere unless the user explicitly asks in the current message or an active user rule.

## Git / GitHub

- Do not run `git push`, `gh pr create`, `gh release create`, or similar remote-publish commands on your own.
- Do not push branches, tags, or commits to origin or any remote.
- Creating local commits is fine only when the user explicitly asks to commit.

## Deployments

- Do not trigger deployments (CI/CD, hosting platforms, server uploads, etc.) unless explicitly requested.
- Do not run deploy scripts or publish artifacts to production/staging environments on your own.

## When the user asks

Only push or deploy after a clear, direct request (e.g. "push this branch", "deploy to staging"). If intent is ambiguous, ask first.
